Alan Pardew and Neil Warnock have a bit of history when it comes to touchline tantrums.

The pair had a brief falling-out when Pardew was in charge of West Ham and Warnock at Sheffield United.

Pardew, of course, was at the centre of two unsavoury incidents last season, the headbutt on Hull’s David Meyler and expletive-laden abuse of Manchester City boss Manuel Pellegrini.

