But while Warnock may be emotionally charged on his return to the dugout with Crystal Palace at St James’ Park on Saturday afternoon, his opposite number will be using his eyes and not his brow to win any sideline dispute.

‘I’m a changed man this year,’ said Pardew. 

‘He gets emotional but I’ve never really had a problem with Neil. I think once at Sheffield United we might have had a bit of an issue, but it didn’t take me long to give him the death stare and he backed off. He knows my death stare is better than his.’

